stimulus:
Welcome and thank you for participating in this study!


In each trial, you will predict whether there will be more RED or BLACK cards.

Afterwards, on the next slide, a deck of 5 cards will appear.


Each card has a 50% chance of appearing as either color.

If you correctly predicted the color of most of the cards, you win the round.

Otherwise, you lose the round.


The next few slides will serve as a tutorial.


Press any key to move on to the next slide.

We will now go through 2 practice rounds.

On the next slide, you will see the words “RED” and “BLACK”.

Click ← on your keyboard to choose “RED” or → to choose “BLACK”.


Please try to stay focused on the fixation cross in the center and reduce blinking during trials.

Press any key to move on to the next slide.

RED
BLACK
+

Chosen option: BLACK

+

Great!

On the following slide, you will see a deck of 5 cards.

The color of each card will be automatically revealed one by one.


If more cards in the deck are in your chosen color than the other color, you win this round.

Otherwise, you lose this round.


Press any key to move on to the next slide.
+
+
+
+
+
+

Whoops, better luck next time!


The next practice trial will be identical to the previous, but you will not be given any instructions.


Please stay focused on the fixation point “+” at the center and blink as little as possible.

BLACK

Chosen option: BLACK

Whoops, better luck next time!


You will now begin with the real trials.
